activity-description.narrative:
Development and adoption of green urban development plans
for the city of Novopolotsk;
Development of pilots on SUT in Novopolotsk and Polotsk; 
Investment in the cycling network;
Investment in improved public transit services;
Investment in bus priority lanes and traffic light synchronization

Development and adoption of green urban development plans
for the city of Polotsk;
Development of pilots on SUT in Polotsk; 
Investment in the cycling network;
Investment in improved public transit services;
Investment in bus priority lanes and traffic light synchronization

comment.narrative:
Outcome 1:
(1) Materials for improving the system of legal regulation and technical regulation in the field of green urban development have been systematized and finalized;
(2) A survey was conducted among residents of Polotsk, Novopolotsk and Novogrudok on the quality of the urban environment;
(3) The following support was provided to the pilot cities (Polotsk, Novopolotsk and Novogrudok) in: (a) monitoring the implementation of green urban development plans using a template; (b) development of requirements for investment sites, taking into account the principles of green urban planning and (c) development of financial proposals for green investment projects;
(4) National and international experience in the field of green urban development was presented and discussed during the final conference of the Project.
Outcome 2: 
(1) A survey of residents of the cities of Polotsk and Novopolotsk was conducted to clarify their awareness of the Projects activities and their attitude to the implementation of activities in the area of sustainable mobility;
(2) Information materials have been prepared for replicating the experience of implementing the activities envisaged by the joint plan for sustainable urban mobility of Polotsk and Novopolotsk in other cities of Belarus;
(3) Audio guides in Russian and English for tourist cycling routes in the cities of Polotsk, Novopolotsk and Novogrudok have been developed;
4) Construction work was carried out to improve the bicycle network and improve the work of public transport in Polotsk and Novopolotsk;
(5) The experience of the project on the development of bicycle infrastructure and improvement of the work of public transport in Polotsk and Novopolotsk is presented in the framework of information and educational events;
(6) Monitoring of the implemented measures for the development of cycling infrastructure and improvement of the work of public transport in Polotsk and Novopolotsk has been arranged.
Outcome 3:
1. Feasibility studies have been prepared for the modernization of street lighting systems in Brest, Vitebsk, Pruzhany, Novopolotsk, Korma, Zelva, Gorodok. Total investment> 10 million US dollars;
2. The smart system equipment for metering the consumption of gas, heat, water and electricity was supplied and installed in Novogrudok for two residential buildings.
3. Monitoring of the operation of equipment for smart metering of heat energy, water and natural gas is being carried out. The equipment is in good working order.
4. Feasibility studies were prepared for the implementation of smart metering systems for resource consumption for 5 additional cities;
5. Experience of the pilot project on installation of smart metering system has been disseminated through the arranged vebinar;
6. The model of municipal energy management system is developed.
Outcome 4: 
(1) Activities to inform and disseminate information on green urban development in the Republic of Belarus among stakeholders have been organized;
(2) The following support has been provided to the pilot municipalities (Korma, Zelva, Gorodok and Krychau):
- monitoring of the implementation of green urban development plans using the template;
- development of the requirements for the investment sites taking into account the principles of green urban planning;
- development of financial proposals for green investment projects.
